      <title>Bethlehem Steel History</title>
      <description>From the New York skyline to the Golden Gate Bridge, the Bethlehem Steel Company built much of America.  When America went to war, the Bethlehem Steel Company built ships and weapons to help defend the US.  When the nation enjoyed peace, Bethlehem built skyscrapers, houses and churches.  Today,  the Bethlehem Steel Company is shutdown and the height of business is a memory for many.  But even as the Lehigh Valley continues to grow and expand in new ways, the importance of the steel industry is not forgotten.</description>
